Bac_luciferase Catalyzes the pyrimidine ring opening between N-3 and C- 4 by an unusual flavin hydroperoxide-catalyzed mechanism to yield ureidoacrylate peracid. Isochorismatase In vivo, quickly hydrolyzes the ureidoacrylate peracid to avoid toxicity, but can also hydrolyzes ureidoacrylate that is formed spontaneously from ureidoacrylate peracid. One of the products of hydrolysis, carbamate, hydrolyzes spontaneously, thereby releasing one of the pyrimidine rings nitrogen atoms as ammonia and one of its carbons as CO2
